{"cursor":"104252","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox Botanical product |image= |caption=Opium poppy fruit exuding latex\nfrom a cut |product=Opium |plant=[[Papaver somniferum]]\n|part=latex|origin=Indochina |active=Morphine, Codeine |producers=Afghanistan\n(primary), Pakistan, Northern India, Thailand, Turkey, Laos, Burma, Mexico,\nColombia, Hungary |consumers=worldwide (#1: U.S.) |wholesale=$3,000 per kilogram\n|retail=$16,000 per kilogram }} 'Opium' ('poppy tears', lachryma papaveris) is\nthe dried latex obtained from the opium poppy (Papaver somniferum). Opium\ncontains approximately 12% morphine, an alkaloid, which is frequently processed\nchemically to produce heroin for the illegal drug trade. The latex also includes\ncodeine and non-narcotic alkaloids such as papaverine, thebaine and noscapine.\nThe traditional method of obtaining the latex is to scratch (\"score\") the\nimmature seed pods (fruits) by hand; the latex leaks out and dries to a sticky\nyellowish residue that is later scraped off. The modern method is to harvest and\nprocess mature plants by machine. \"Meconium\" historically referred to related,\nweaker preparations made from other parts of the poppy or different species of\npoppies. [http://www.hon.ch/Dossier/MotherChild/labor_complications/birth_m-\neconium.html Health on the Net Foundation Mother and Child Glossary]\n\nThe production of opium itself has not changed since ancient times. Through\nselective breeding of the Papaver somniferum plant, the content of the\nphenanthrene alkaloids morphine, codeine, and to a lesser extent thebaine, has\nbeen greatly increased. In modern times, much of the thebaine, which often\nserves as the raw material for the synthesis for hydrocodone, hydromorphone, and\nother semi-synthetic opiates, originates from extracting [[Papaver orientale]]\nor [[Papaver bracteatum]].\n\nOpium for illegal use is often converted into heroin, which is less bulky,\nmaking it easier to smuggle, and which multiplies its potency to approximately\ntwice that of morphine. Heroin can be taken by intravenous injection,\nintranasally, or smoked (vaporized) and inhaled.\n","linknr":1407,"url":"Opium","recorded":1362373143,"links":120,"instances":["medicine","music","christian","fiction","title","mythology","witchcraft","southeast_asia","author","plant","medicine","author","19th_century"],"pdf":["http://www.unodc.org/pdf/research/wdr07/WDR_2007_3.1.1_afghanistan.pdf","http://www.unodc.org/pdf/research/wdr07/WDR_2007_3.1.1_afghanistan.pdf","http://www.unodc.org/pdf/research/wdr07/WDR_2007_1.2_opium_heroin.pdf","http://www.unodc.org/pdf/research/wdr07/WDR_2007_1.2_opium_heroin.pdf","http://www.humanities.qut.edu.au/research/socialchange/docs/conf_papers2002/TrockiCarl.pdf","http://www.humanities.qut.edu.au/research/socialchange/docs/conf_papers2002/TrockiCarl.pdf","http://web.archive.org/web/20080822032249/http://www.nida.nih.gov/PDF/DARHW/033-052_Kandall.pdf","http://www.nida.nih.gov/PDF/DARHW/033-052_Kandall.pdf","http://web.archive.org/web/20080822032249/http://www.nida.nih.gov/PDF/DARHW/033-052_Kandall.pdf","http://www.dur.ac.uk/chinese.politics/Public%20lectures/William%20A%20Callahan%20RenDa%20Lecture.pdf","http://www.dur.ac.uk/chinese.politics/Public%20lectures/William%20A%20Callahan%20RenDa%20Lecture.pdf","http://www.unodc.org/pdf/WDR_2005/volume_1_chap1_opium.pdf","http://www.unodc.org/pdf/WDR_2005/volume_1_chap1_opium.pdf","http://www.ungassondrugs.org/images/stories/brief26.pdf"],"categories":["Euphoriants","Medicinal plants","Morphine","Opium|"],"headings":["History","Modern production and usage","Chemical and physiological properties","Slang terms","Literary cultural references","See also","References","Further reading","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/2a/Slaapbol_R0017601.JPG/180px-Slaapbol_R0017601.JPG","//uploa